This is intended to guide users on how to use GIT

=====================================================================================
Local Procedures
=====================================================================================
1. Adding a new file / Folder

- Create file
- git status // to see the status
- git add [filename/dir]
- git reset HEAD [filename/dir] // This unstages the file 
- git diff // Shows the changes made to the file btn staging area and working area
- git commit // To commit changes, this opens an editor 


2. Staging modified files
- git add [filename/dir]

3.Removing files
- git rm [filename/dir] // Removes the file/folder
- git rm log/\*.log // Removes all files with .log on the /log dir

4. Renaming files
- git mv README.txt README // Renames README.txt to README

5. Look at the history 
- git log 
- git log -p // Shows the diff 
- git log -2 // Limits to last 2 entries
- git log --stat // Shows some statistics 

6. Undoing stuff
- git commit --amend // Enables to make a few changes to the last commit
- git checkout -- [filename] // Discards changes  * Very risky, don't really use it. 


=====================================================================================
Going Remote:
=====================================================================================
1. See all the remote servers
- git remote 
- git remote -v // shows the url 

2. Adding remote Repos
- git remote add [shortname] [url]

3. Fetching
- git fetch [remote-name] // Just fetches remote files from server 
- git pull [remote-name] // Fetches and tries to merge changes 


